Package: PrevKalman
Title: Horvitz-Thompson Prevalence Estimation with Kalman Filtering and Smoothing
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Jeongjin",
           family = "Lee",
           email = "Jeongjin95@users.noreply.github.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for simulation, Horvitz-Thompson prevalence estimation,
    block jackknife uncertainty quantification, and Kalman filtering and
    smoothing for repeated infectious disease surveillance data. The package
    is based on the workflow developed for the manuscript "Kalman Filtering
    and Smoothing for Improving Precision in Horvitz--Thompson Estimation of
    Infectious Disease Prevalence".
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: https://github.com/Jeongjin95/PrevKalman
BugReports: https://github.com/Jeongjin95/PrevKalman/issues
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.1)
Imports:
    parallel,
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
